From b33b29eda9a0be9fbcf8ecb4b4892cf4c053c209 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 22:19:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Align dashboard with app Firebase schema, fix broken data
 flows, add missing features
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Schema alignment:
- Eliminate phantom 'caregivers' collection — derive caregivers from users with role
- Fix AuthContext to use DB role as single source of truth (not custom claims)
- Fix Login to route by DB role instead of custom claims
- Fix Signup to write role field to users/{uid}
- Fix all log views to read targetUserId/carerId (matching app) instead of userId
- Add name field handling with getUserDisplayName() fallback
- Add shared schema constants (src/shared/schema.js) documenting all data contracts

Broken flow fixes:
- UserManagement: remove push() user creation (was creating phantom records)
- UserManagement: use unified users collection for caregiver assignment
- Caregivers page: redirect to UserManagement
- ConnectUser: filter out caregivers/admins from unassigned users list
- Dashboard logger: remove AsyncStorage import, use Firebase directly
- Logs: add CSV export, level/action filters, session ID display

New features:
- Feedback page: view user feedback from the app
- UserSettings page: view per-user AAC app preferences
- Caregiver dashboard: show recent activity logs for assigned users
- Admin dashboard: 4-card summary stats, user name resolution in charts/tables
- Role management: inline role change in UserManagement

